STICKING AROUND 
I always imagined I would die in my younger-older age, maybe around 65. Full #Openjournal on www.patreon.com/movmeant .... Yet inside I don‚Äôt feel disappointed. I‚Äôve been here before many times in my life. I understand that it‚Äôs lack of understanding. That nagging feeling I spoke of earlier is back, it‚Äôs the fear of being DIFFERENT. It takes me right back to eleven year old Cuchi. Sitting in the back of the classroom terrified the teacher would call my name to read out loud! That all eyes would then be on me. I preferred and still prefer staying in my world. I never felt of this world. I always felt different, like I didn‚Äôt belong. This never bothered me as some would imagine. I loved/love being alone. I‚Äôm never bored. My mind and body transport to other worlds very easily. I actually prefer it over there. Its a creative world where I don‚Äôt think, I just exist in art and love. It‚Äôs complex and simple all at once. It‚Äôs a hard place to explain unless you‚Äôve visited.
